M.G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 18.proposition: This action arises under the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, specifically M.G.L. c. 186, § 18, which guarantees a tenant the right to quiet enjoyment of the leased premises.

M.G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Plaintiff asserts a single cause of action for Breach of the Covenant of Quiet Enjoyment under Massachusetts law, as codified in M.G.L. c. 186, § 14, citing Defendant's failure to maintain basic security measures on the leased premises, resulting in the infringement of Plaintiff's right to peaceable possession and enjoyment of the property.
